benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/admin/invoices - Trigger an invoice generation for all parked accounts

covered: Valid Request coverage through multiple successful scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC04, TC10, TC12, TC13, TC16, TC17, TC18).
Query Parameters and Validation coverage (offset/limit valid, invalid values, non-integer tests in TC06, TC07).
Error handling coverage for common scenarios (TC05 missing header, TC08 unauthorized, TC09 service unavailability).
Edge cases coverage (TC10 max limit, TC11 extra parameters, TC12 large volume with performance note, TC13 partial input, TC14 security header injection).
Regression scenarios (TC16 header parsing, TC17 backward compatibility).
Performance considerations (TC12 large data volume with response time note, TC18 concurrency).
Recovery from transient failures (TC15 retry semantics).
gaps: Large-scale pagination handling beyond simple offset/limit (no explicit tests validating repeated or cursor-based pagination behavior across many pages).
Invalid payload validation scenarios (malformed or missing required fields within the JSON body are not explicitly covered beyond header/param validation).
Duplicate submission handling (idempotency or deduplication of repeated POSTs not tested).
Server error / 500 Internal Server Error scenarios not explicitly covered (only 503/service unavailability).
Caching behavior tests (ETag/Cache-Control headers or similar caching semantics not covered).
Rate limiting/throttling tests (no explicit tests asserting behavior under rapid consecutive requests).
recommendations: Add explicit tests for invalid payload structures (malformed JSON, missing required fields in body) to validate 400 responses and proper validation messages.
Add a test for 500 Internal Server Error simulation to ensure proper server error handling and messaging (beyond 503).
Add tests for idempotency/duplicate submissions to confirm no duplicate invoices are generated on retry or repeated requests.
Introduce caching tests (ETag/Cache-Control) to confirm caching headers and behavior where applicable.
Add rate limiting tests to verify system behavior under bursty traffic (e.g., multiple concurrent requests within a short window).
Extend pagination tests to cover deeper pagination across multiple pages and edge cases (e.g., offset beyond range, negative values beyond validation, end-of-list behavior).
Consider explicit tests for 400/401/403 edge cases with more granular error messages to ensure consistent client feedback.
